Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.62,0:00:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you like semiotics?\NIsn't there a nice new word?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.30,0:00:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody know what semiotics means?\NAt least we've got an audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.35,0:00:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the science of structure of language, yeah?\NLanguaging and the science of labels and structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.39,0:00:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What is truth?\NIt depends on language wording.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.39,0:00:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a man who's written a book all about words\Nand the importance that it plays in politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.49,0:01:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's whether you call people illegals or undocumented.\NTotally changes the picture, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.01,0:01:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of all the war, political wars that go over.\NAre they undocumented or are they illegal?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.15,0:01:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I solved it very simply.\NI said they're both.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.16,0:01:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They're undocumented illegals.\NThen they jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.21,0:01:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, therefore, you must be anti-Mexican.\NYou see how they distort it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.13,0:01:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with being Mexican.\NNothing to do with being Mexican.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.30,0:01:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All Americans I know are crazy about them, love them.\NWe all use them, hang out with them, and chat with them, and love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.30,0:01:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with being Mexican at all.\NIt has to do with the fact that as an employer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.94,0:01:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get into big trouble if you hire them.\NThat's what it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All you want to know is do they have a green card or not?\NBecause if they don't, you can get busted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.90,0:02:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So semiotics, that means politically,\Nyou play with the words to try and create a different impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forget the name of the book.\NThe guy's an advisor to a lot of political groups, I guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.22,0:02:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,on how to use a different word.\NA different word will give a different inference.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.88,0:02:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So just your selection of vocabulary already changes the reality\Nor the seeming reality just by semiotics.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Semiotics is the science of how language,\Nand vocabulary is structured.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.68,0:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is truth depends on your own intention,\Nyour dedication, and your humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.40,0:02:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now realizing that God and truth are one and the same thing,\Nthat God is really the highest truth possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.58,0:02:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you just take things, calibrate everything in the universe,\Nand keep following whichever calibrates the highest,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.64,0:03:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you will end up with God.\NSo just following truth itself will eventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.20,0:03:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,take you to divinity.\NDivinity is the ultimate then, and it calibrates at infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.64,0:03:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you follow truth itself, truth itself even just intellectually,\Nyou end up with divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.72,0:03:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You end up with the obvious things that it is impossible for non-life to create life.\NSo the materialist is stuck with the fact that life, how does life arise?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.39,0:03:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Reductionist, semiotics, you cannot get life from non-life.\NAnd people say, well, all the chemicals just fell together and life suddenly happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.16,0:03:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that life is of a different dimension.\NThey're not the same dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.38,0:04:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's mixing levels.\NThe material non-living matter itself is a different level than life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.43,0:04:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So matter cannot be destroyed.\NIt can only change.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.45,0:04:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Form life itself cannot be destroyed.\NWe can't repeat that too often.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.34,0:04:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I have permission to ask this.\NIt is impossible for life to be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.79,0:04:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist that is true at the level of infinity.\NResist at the level of infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And thank you.\NWe've done this many times to confirm because it's a very important understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.74,0:04:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Life can only change form.\NIt cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.27,0:04:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nat physical,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.77,0:04:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at physical death where dust returns to dust,\Nyou can't die because death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.78,0:04:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only change form.\NIn an infinite universe then,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.71,0:04:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,with no beginning and no end and no intrinsic causality,\Nthe only thing that can happen is it changes form.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.13,0:05:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the law of conservation of energy is that energies can only change form.\NLaw of conservation of matter is that matter can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.27,0:05:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of conservation of life,\Nwhich seems starkly obvious,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.23,0:05:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you cannot destroy life.\NIt can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.23,0:05:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, you don't have to feel so guilty about swarming the fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.87,0:05:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NWhack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.70,0:05:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He just leaves his physical body and his etheric body and he doesn't even notice.\NThe fly doesn't even notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.45,0:05:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NThe fly doesn't even notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes flying in his etheric body and that's what he experiences as me all along.\NSo nothing's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.51,0:05:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NA couple of times I went out of body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.38,0:05:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never even heard of being out of body.\NI was out of body and never even heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.38,0:05:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Being gravely ill.\NSuddenly found myself outside the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.38,0:06:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Never heard of it.\NNothing changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.66,0:06:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was still me.\NI was myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I had all my faculties.\NI could see, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.98,0:06:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I could move around in the room.\NI could be up in the ceiling looking down at the audience now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I laid down and went out of body,\NI could go up there and watch the audience there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.66,0:06:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I could go over there.\NI could then go over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.66,0:06:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very neat.\NYou don't have to drag your body with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course a lot of research has been done on this because of its implications for surgery.\NAnd people may have made agreements.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If they go out of body, they'll go up on top of the bookcase there and tell you what's on.\NAnd they come back after the surgery, come back in the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.65,0:06:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll tell you what's on top of the bookcase.\NSo anyway, death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.02,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get death at zero at all.\NYou get neutrality at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:07:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ashes that you return to calibrate at 200,\Nand your spirit stays the same as whatever it was when you left the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.54,0:07:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go to the spirit world where below 200 are the levels of hell.\NAnd did I say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That kid who calibrated at the lowest I've ever calibrated anything,\Nthe Green River Killer was about 10 or 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.14,0:07:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid was 5.\N5.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.14,0:07:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw a demon like that.\NThat's a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.14,0:07:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go to that which you are.\NYou only obviously gravitate when you leave the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.17,0:07:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only gravitate to that which you are.\NYou can't gravitate to that which you are not, could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.17,0:07:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot become an impossibility.\NYou can only fulfill a potentiality and a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.20,0:07:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So you merely experience yourself\Nat the level of who you are and what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.39,0:07:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the body is there or not.\NIn fact, you won't even like the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.39,0:08:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've noticed the times that I did go out of body,\NI had no attraction to it whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.39,0:08:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd think, gee whiz, I'd be wanting to get back in the body.\NI looked at Dave laying in the bed and I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.39,0:08:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,God almighty, he looks poorly.\NI had no ambition at all to reconnect with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.65,0:08:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't connect with that body laying there as you at all.\NYou have no attraction to it, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.65,0:08:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I have more attraction to a kitty.\NI'd be in a panic if my kitty was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.65,0:08:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But my own body was no attraction to it at all.\NAnd I went out of the body several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.87,0:08:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I later learned how to do it,\Nas many as some of the people in the group here have done that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.87,0:08:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and gone to the Western Recall Institute.\NWho wrote Journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.13,0:08:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?\NMonroe, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Journey's Out of the Body, yeah.\NBy Monroe, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.76,0:08:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So after I went out of the body, I read that,\Nand then I learned how to do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.76,0:08:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and learned how to do it.\NLearned how to do it in a hypnotic state,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:09:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I went and studied it at the Monroe Institute.\NAnd so that removes any doubt in your mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're a physical entity or a spirit.\NBecause the minute you're out of the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.86,0:09:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that you're not that body.\NSo death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.18,0:09:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We say that over and over again,\Nbecause mankind has such a belief in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.75,0:09:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the capacity for comprehension,\Nin the abstract categories,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.90,0:09:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kantian categories,\Nand that's another mistake that academia,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.90,0:09:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's not academia, it's the far left,\Nand its impact on academia,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.90,0:09:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they mix categories.\NWhat's true at one level is not true on another,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.00,0:09:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,not only spiritually,\Nbut the abstract levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.06,0:09:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A family and a genus and a species,\Nyou can't just mix them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A species is not a genus, and a genus is not...\NYou can't mix levels of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So your intention then,\Nyour dedication,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:10:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is to truth for its own sake.\NSo if we do a calibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.74,0:10:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind has no interest in the outcome.\NBecause I'm just as curious
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what's going to come up as she is.\NBoth of us here, we don't have any idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.93,0:10:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We can often guess it,\Nhaving done it so many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.70,0:10:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I looked at the cement,\Nit looked like 200 to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.70,0:10:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, 200 came to my mind.\NIt's just because having done it so many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.72,0:10:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get better and better at it as you do it.\NThe higher your consciousness evolves,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.72,0:10:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the better you are at it.\NAnd of course, like riding a bicycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.72,0:10:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,practice makes perfect.\NPractice makes perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.78,0:10:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we do is I ask,\Ndo we have permission to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.78,0:10:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I ask it mentally if I don't verbalize it.\NI have permission to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.78,0:10:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to get a yes.\NThen I put it in the form of a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.78,0:11:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ask a question.\NI put it in the form of a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.88,0:11:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the statement is either true or false.\NThe energy runs down our arm
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.91,0:11:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,like electricity very rapidly.\NSo you can't ask the question
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.91,0:11:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then hang out and scratch on yourself\Nand then push down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.00,0:11:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to help people get better results.\NYou have to be dedicated to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.06,0:11:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and not a positionality.\NYou have to really want to know what is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell people,\Nfirst find out what is the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.06,0:11:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then worry about what you're going to do about it later.\NThat the stock that you just bought
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.22,0:11:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 160.\NAnd now worry about it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.51,0:11:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't try and influence the arm\Nso that that stock you just bought
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.51,0:11:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 200.\NIt's better to know the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can sell it long or short or some trick.\NAnd get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.70,0:12:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides they got lawyers now that advertise\Nif you lost money on the stock market call me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.12,0:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have the busiest offices in the world.\NIf you lost any money in investments
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.18,0:12:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,call Fregit and Fregit and Fregit.\NWow, I don't know how they can put up an ad like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.14,0:12:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so your dedication to God\Nand reality has to be high.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.30,0:12:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Your capacity for comprehension\Nabstract categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.30,0:12:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you cannot jump the Kantian categories.\NThe Kantian categories have to do phylum,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.30,0:12:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,class, species, etc.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.50,0:12:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all paradigms too.\NYou can't mix them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.50,0:12:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and say that a fish is a better bird.\NA fish is a bird without feathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.39,0:12:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't say that.\NThat's what the far left does.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.16,0:12:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They say a fish is a bird without feathers\Nand it's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:13:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll pass a law.\NThey love the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get the ACLU to handle it.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.38,0:13:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sue in the right of birds.\NEpistemology, sophistication, education and priorities
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.78,0:13:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,will influence the result.\NThe capacity to do consciousness calibration
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.88,0:13:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,arises with more education, the more dedication,\Nthe more spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.88,0:13:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all of those, the spiritual evolution\Nis the most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Education would really give you sophistication\Nin how to best phrase the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How to best phrase the question.\NSo by sophisticated phrasing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.91,0:13:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're likely to get more truth\Njust because you're expressing the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.91,0:13:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Which would be reflective somewhat of IQ.\NAnother thing that may interfere is personality blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.03,0:14:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, opposition.\NOppositionalism, contrariness and hostility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.03,0:14:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Contrariness, contrariness.\NAnd oppositionalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.38,0:14:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There are oppositional, contrary people.\NThere are people who have compartmentalized personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.51,0:14:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking of one now.\NIt calibrates around 395.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.51,0:14:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he's got a compartmentalized personality\Nthat calibrates about 90 or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.95,0:14:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So one part of him is reasonable\Nand sensible and normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.95,0:14:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And one part of him is sort of a black alter ego\Nthat writes nasty blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.14,0:14:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that would be fun to write nasty blogs.\NI could write nasty blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.62,0:14:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought of doing that.\NFun thing, you know, fun thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.62,0:14:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NWhat haven't you done in the world that would be fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:15:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how about writing nasty blogs?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.84,0:15:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because of your own sophistication\Nand education and priorities,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.84,0:15:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't find yourself able to do that.\NBut IQ does give you a chance to think of things
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that other people would not think of.\NThat's really what it amounts to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.03,0:15:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They would not think of it,\Nbut you would instantly see the connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.03,0:15:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So personality blocks,\Nthere's a lot of personality disorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.42,0:15:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what percentage\Nin the latest American Psychiatric Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.42,0:15:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like 29%.\NSomething like 29% of the public
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.42,0:15:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,have personality disorders.\NPassivity, aggression, oppositionalism,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.42,0:15:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,contrariness, innate hostility.\NSome people are just hostile all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.58,0:15:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thing to do is just avoid them.\NThe problem in today's society is via the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.70,0:16:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is supposedly fair and balanced.\NNow the problem, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.98,0:16:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably going to lead to the downfall\Nof democracy over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.42,0:16:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If you give falsehood equal power to truth\Nand equal validity to truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you will end up at a gridlock.\NWhat is the current Congress?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Gridlock Congress.\NWhatever this one wants to do, the other blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a do-nothing Congress.\NI was in this Congress to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.80,0:16:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing of any importance anyway.\NThey can't even put a fence around the in-house
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.06,0:16:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so the coyotes don't get them.\NWe do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.18,0:16:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We put a fence around our chicken coop.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.43,0:16:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we have bobcats that come and eat them.\NAnd we have coyotes that come and eat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.01,0:17:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we put a fence around them.\NPeople say, well, a fence wouldn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Works around a penitentiary, don't it?\NWorks around the playground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Works in my backyard.\NWorks around the doghouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.12,0:17:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeps the javelina out of my tomatoes.\NIs that prejudice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.20,0:17:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not unless you mislabel it as prejudice.\NIt's got nothing to do with prejudice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.20,0:17:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Got nothing to do with nationality.\NThose are all the distortions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Distortions.\NDoesn't have anything to do with Mexicanism
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.97,0:17:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or any other kind of ism.\NIt has to do with what you consider sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.35,0:17:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,See, every time the government breaks\Nits own and fails to obey its own laws,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.35,0:17:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it loses its sovereignty.\NA government to function has to have sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.92,0:18:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be gridlocked, what happens is you end up losing\Nyour sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.24,0:18:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The sovereignty.\NAnd you lose the respect to the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.24,0:18:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If the government doesn't respect its own laws,\Nwhy should we?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.20,0:18:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If the cop don't obey the law,\NI might as well steal a couple of hamburgers myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NSo the calibrated level of consciousness then would fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.70,0:18:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you pass a law and do not obey it or implement it,\Nthe consciousness level and your power drops.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.70,0:18:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you constantly negate yourself,\Nconstantly self-negation,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.70,0:18:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you eventually put yourself out of the game.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.30,0:18:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we talked a lot about postmodernism\Nand the fallacy of moral equivalency,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.30,0:18:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the moral equivalency is the game of,\Nof falsity and multiculturalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.30,0:18:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things calibrate below 200.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.34,0:19:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they sound, they sound good,\Nbut then when implemented,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.34,0:19:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize they're based upon relativistic falsities.\NThe fall of academia we already spoke about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.69,0:19:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got delusional professors.\NI can't believe paying somebody thousands of dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.69,0:19:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to give a lecture when he's frankly psychotic.\NWe used to put them away in the back,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.14,0:19:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in the back ward,\Nput them on penicillin to cure their brain syphilis
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or anti-psychotics.\NNow they get $50,000 to lecture at the university.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.78,0:19:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot believe what goes on.\NI keep pinching myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.78,0:19:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I can't believe what goes on in Colorado\Nand various universities,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,even good old University of Wisconsin.\NGod help us, University of Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.26,0:19:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us all pray for the University of Wisconsin.\NTexas A&M calibrates at 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.06,0:20:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Texas A&M calibrates at 440.\NDuke University, less than 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.75,0:20:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So where do you send your kids?\NBig 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.77,0:20:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But University of Wisconsin,\NI'm going to send them a letter
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.90,0:20:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm dropping them for my will.\NI am not, after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.04,0:20:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,going to leave them $10 million.\NBut that would be a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.62,0:20:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to retaliate.\NI still got to put a psychotic professor on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.69,0:20:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,pay out good taxpayer money.\NGood old University of Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.69,0:20:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly.\NUniversity of Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.13,0:21:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All the stories we could tell about college days, right?\NSo, anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.28,0:21:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to tell you a story about University of Wisconsin,\Nbut I better not, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.19,0:21:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My friend, my friend...\NMy friend Hooper and I,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.45,0:21:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooper is now a deceased college friend.\NWe met in the service,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.54,0:21:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and after the service,\Nwe were going to college,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.54,0:21:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and my first car,\NI paid $35 for a Chevy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.54,0:21:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,two-seater coupe,\Nand it ran out of oil on the highway
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.80,0:21:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and blew, blew the block,\Nblew the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.96,0:21:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so we ended up at the...\NIt was homecoming weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.02,0:21:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at the University Rathskeller.\NBetween the...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.54,0:21:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,People were so poor in those days,\Nyou folks wouldn't even believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.54,0:21:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Between the two of us,\Nwe had 10 cents, period.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a nickel, I had a nickel.\NSo we bought a schooner beer for 10 cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.78,0:21:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sitting there,\Noverlooking Lake Mendota
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.78,0:22:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Rathskeller,\Nand we're sitting there outside in the sunshine,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.78,0:22:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden, ploop.\NDamn, bird pooped right in the middle of the schooner beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.22,0:22:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't like he had another dime,\Nand you can say...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.22,0:22:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I looked at Hooper,\Nand I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.60,0:22:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I'll get a spoon.\NSo we got...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.55,0:22:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a soup spoon from the Rathskeller,\Nand it floated like a glob
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.55,0:22:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the middle of the beer.\NAnd carefully scooped it out and flipped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.80,0:23:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And said, won't kill us anyway.\NSo we split it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.73,0:23:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I like the La Boheme,\NI think, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.73,0:23:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the La Boheme in the movie.\NThe starving students in the...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.73,0:23:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're breaking up the furniture\Nto keep the place warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.73,0:23:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Having lived the penniless student days, you know.\NI said, well, it won't kill us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.18,0:23:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the bird doesn't have anything like syphilis\Nor to be or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.78,0:23:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo we've had enough delusional professors
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.14,0:23:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,at Duke University, University of Wisconsin.\NColorado is, of course, the most...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.23,0:23:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hear what those guys are getting paid a year,\Nthen it gets you peed a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.23,0:23:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, 150,000 a year to do nothing\Nexcept walk around pouting delusions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.36,0:23:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrate 160 or something like that.\NThere's the...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.45,0:23:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to deal with the fall of consciousness level\Nin the U.S. and the Western civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:24:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world of recent times.\NYou know, even since we began giving these lectures...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.45,0:24:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, permission to ask in front of this group.\NEven since we began giving these lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.70,0:24:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of the United States\Nhas dropped over four points,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.70,0:24:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,five points, six points.\NThe consciousness level of the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.12,0:24:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has dropped five points.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.12,0:24:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of man,\Nmankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.12,0:24:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has dropped over four points,\Nfive points.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.12,0:24:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Four points, mankind.\NSo it's Western civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.12,0:24:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Western civilization has dropped over four points,\Nfive points.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.15,0:24:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The fall of level of consciousness\Nof Western civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.15,0:24:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and its expression in America,\Nfour or five points,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.95,0:24:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't sound like much,\Nbut four or five points can make quite a bit of difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.95,0:24:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If you raise the level of the sea\Nfour and a half, five, five percent,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.95,0:24:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to affect all the ships afloat.\NSo we have to be attentive
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.75,0:25:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to the integrity of the intellectual level,\Nnot just the spiritual level,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.75,0:25:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not the political level,\Nbut the scholasticism of the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.88,0:25:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have an authority on it right now,\Nsitting in the corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.16,0:25:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who reports back on what's going on in academia.\NSo academia can't pull the wool over any...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.16,0:25:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,on Neo anymore,\Nbecause I have my own spy right in their midst.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.18,0:25:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me about...\NI wrote that book on capitalism, 1770-something.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.85,0:25:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wealth of Nations.\NSo I've got my own informants
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.49,0:25:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the...\Nlocked into academia.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.49,0:25:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're not going to get away with anything\Nwithout our knowing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.49,0:25:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just want you to know,\NI'm not just talking from hearsay,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.77,0:26:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've got my own informants,\Nbut I've got my own informants.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.43,0:26:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thing looks like depends on how it's contextualized.\NAnd in modern terminology,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.04,0:26:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it's talked about the impact of framing.\NThe same picture in this frame
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.04,0:26:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,conveys a completely different message than in this frame.\NAnd this is one of the political manipulations of fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.04,0:26:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You take this image,\Nyou put it in this frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.04,0:26:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, isn't that awful?\NYou put it in a different frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.04,0:26:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, isn't that swell?\NThe content, the truth hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.80,0:26:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you put it in a different framework.\NNow it looks horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.80,0:26:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,People made such and such amount of money.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.37,0:26:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In that framework,\Ncompared to the U.S. economy,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.37,0:26:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it sounds very little.\NCompared to what I lived on as a student,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.23,0:26:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say compared to what other cultures live on,\Nit's a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.23,0:27:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a lot or is it a little?\NWell, it depends on how you want to frame it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.30,0:27:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The other framing, of course, is over time.\NOver time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.55,0:27:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And this history of the United States,\Nyou know, is based on
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.65,0:27:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance of the things that were written\Nand their impact has to be framed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.65,0:27:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in tension of the founders of the country.\NThe country was founded by pilgrims
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.35,0:27:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,who were looking for religious freedom.\NThis country was founded by pilgrims.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.77,0:27:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Pilgrims.\NOf course, then they go on to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.60,0:27:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they killed all the Indians.\NSo how you want to frame it then
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.96,0:27:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,makes it look either good or not so good.\NThe impact of framing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.99,0:27:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is where ingenuity, cleverness,\Nand we're having a person
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.99,0:28:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who really knows how to lie with expertise.\NThis is the way you lie with great expertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.50,0:28:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I pick sequence.\NYou know that 50%
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.75,0:28:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of the personal ideas of criminal suspects\Nare fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.14,0:28:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The error in recognizing\Nthe guilty from the non-guilty is 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.14,0:28:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So that recent thing that arose\Nbecause of the DNA that went around to the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.58,0:28:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,death throes of all the prisons.\NWhat's the name of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.74,0:28:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The something project.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.70,0:28:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Innocence project, is it?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.71,0:28:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So they found what?\N97 people condemned to death
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.71,0:28:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the DNA proved\Nthere wasn't even a possibility for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.71,0:28:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're going to have to admit the perpetrator.\NSo the error rate just in visual recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.13,0:28:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is already 50%.\NThe impact of the framing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.19,0:28:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The sequence in which you show the,\Nlet's say the supposed witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.19,0:29:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The sequence in which you show him\Nthe photographs of possible suspects
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.19,0:29:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,already influences\Nwho they think is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.19,0:29:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the sequence in which you look at the pictures\Nwill now influence what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.14,0:29:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, he looks just like the guy.\NIf you framed him a different way,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.14,0:29:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,he wouldn't look like the guy.\NSo you see the chance of error.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.65,0:29:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Without consciousness calibration,\Nyou can't really know the truth of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.65,0:29:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's what it all amounts to.\NThis is from ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.10,0:29:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There are three things involved\Nin conveying information.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.19,0:29:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Logos, ethos, and pathos.\NOne has to do with the integrity of the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.29,0:29:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity of the speaker.\NHow to calibrate the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.80,0:30:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate the level of truth of the speaker.\NThen, the efficacy of the speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.10,0:30:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one thing to know a matter.\NIt's another to convey it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.10,0:30:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How efficacious is the presentation?\NAnd the third thing is in classic Greece
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.62,0:30:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,called pathos.\NThat is the receptivity of the listener.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.62,0:30:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't do any good to explain\Nthe advanced theoretical physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.48,0:30:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The school of idiots with IQs of 70.\NSo it means you have to have the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.67,0:30:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to comprehend.\NThen you have to have the capacity to express.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.67,0:30:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And you yourself must come from integrity.\NSo to be a convincing speaker then,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.70,0:30:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,this was used to train politicians,\Nalso trained to teach them how to evade that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.70,0:30:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we evade that?\NAnd so,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.77,0:30:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,this is how convincing is his honesty.\NThis is how efficacious is his message.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.57,0:31:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the listenability of the audience.\NAnd when you listen to political speeches
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.75,0:31:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always good to just run those three through your mind.\NThe way you develop a scholastic education
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.75,0:31:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is you get just an important concept\Nand then you apply it in everyday life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.75,0:31:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,until you begin to see it through those eyes.\NThere are politicians that are just great.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.75,0:31:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're great out there.\NAnd there are people that are very logical,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.13,0:31:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous,\Nbut nobody's willing to listen to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.42,0:31:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Pathos.\NSo they miscalculated the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.58,0:31:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't give a lecture on this level\Nto an audience on that level, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.06,0:31:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Logos, ethos, and pathos means then.\NAnd we can think of very prominent politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.06,0:31:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that are very slick at their presentation,\Nbut unconvincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.06,0:31:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And some that are very logical.\NAnd then some that are not logical,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.25,0:32:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but you'll love them anyway.\NAnd what did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.44,0:32:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NOne minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.87,0:32:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NDeism, atheism, and accountability.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.87,0:32:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already somewhat...\NI wouldn't trust anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.87,0:32:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't believe in God on a certain level.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.87,0:32:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're not answerable.\NThey're not answerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.94,0:32:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're lucky, they have intellectual integrity.\NIntellectual integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.94,0:32:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's possible to be an atheist\Nand to be quite accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.13,0:32:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's thinking of it more or less like a class\Nin which you're debating class.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.70,0:32:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So at least he has allegiance to intellectual excellence.\NSo the intellectual can certainly satisfy criteria
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.70,0:32:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,by being intellectually accountable.\NBut in the long run,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.93,0:32:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only...\NIt's only the inner knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.12,0:33:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that every hair on your head shall be counted\Nthat keeps you strictly pulled back
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.60,0:33:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to the magnet of truth.\NEvery hair on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.60,0:33:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do this.\NIt is an absolute truth at the level of infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.70,0:33:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Every hair on your head shall be counted.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.66,0:33:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In case there's any doubt.\NWe've done this over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.69,0:33:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It says,\Nevery hair on your head shall be counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.10,0:33:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NSo when you take responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.60,0:33:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for the significance and meaning of that.\NSo the reason you can't trust atheists at a certain level
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.60,0:33:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is because they do not think they're going to be accountable.\NYou can screw your brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.60,0:33:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,get high like hell and get away with it,\Nand you're going to get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.02,0:33:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not accountable.\NNow, I'm not going to teach anything of really great truth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.02,0:33:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to anybody that doesn't respect it,\Nand they're not going to respect it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.02,0:33:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're not accountable.\NSo you see people out there selling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.30,0:34:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how some of these so-called groups,\Nthese gurus that were so famous,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.37,0:34:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,have crashed so badly.\NI mean, how can you ignore the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.37,0:34:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that you know you're accountable?\NI don't really get that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.43,0:34:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean these spiritual teachers\Nwere actually atheists all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.43,0:34:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what goes on.\NSome world-famous gurus, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.43,0:34:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,full stunts that are just,\Nmake you aghast, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.43,0:34:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only explanation I can give for it\Nis a satanic attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.43,0:34:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they were in a high place\Nand influencing goodness,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.53,0:34:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically or someplace,\Nthey had a chink in their armor,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.53,0:34:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and zap, the demons got them.\NSo as we move ahead in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.85,0:34:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and our own spiritual illusion,\Nwe watch for the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.85,0:34:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the temptation?\NThat's just a fancy word for temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.85,0:34:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the temptation here?\NI remember the knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.85,0:34:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that now I am beyond all karma.\NNow I'm beyond karmic accountability.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.85,0:35:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that came as a silent knowingness.\NOut of absolute stillness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.64,0:35:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours.\NYou're not accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.64,0:35:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no karma.\NOwn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.53,0:35:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw who'd owned it.\NAnd I saw who went through this high pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.01,0:35:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not many.\NAnd I saw Jesus Christ denied it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.01,0:35:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw who denied it.\NAnd this is all in absolute silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.19,0:35:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no thinkingness or knowingness,\Nthoughtness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.19,0:35:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a knowingness of who passed through this pass.\NIt's a high level pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.19,0:35:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours.\NOwn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.54,0:35:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NTalk about the temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.74,0:35:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the temptation that they fell for.\NAll power over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.73,0:35:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All power over others.\NYou see, if you negate love as a reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.73,0:36:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,now nobody has any power over you\Nbecause a decent person will stop just out of lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.21,0:36:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't torture a dog to death\Njust out of lovingness for all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.21,0:36:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say, well, that's just an attachment,\Nthat's just wanting to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.50,0:36:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll negate that.\NNow you can torture dogs and not feel guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.94,0:36:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours.\NYou're not answerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.94,0:36:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a high pass, last ditch temptation.\NAnd it's one of the demons that attacked the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.65,0:36:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,attacked Jesus Christ.\NAll power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.51,0:36:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no accountability.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.51,0:36:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know what happens.\NI don't know what happens if you take the wrong turn there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.99,0:36:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to think of the consequences.\NAnyway, the fact that you're accountable then is what a safeguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.16,0:36:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that you want to live fearfully,\Nfearful of making a mistake or fearful of a sin or something
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.16,0:37:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because along with accountability also goes forgiveness.\NJesus Christ died for you to be easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.61,0:37:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He speaks for you.\NAnd because forgiveness is part of your inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.61,0:37:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So as a devoted spiritual student,\Nyou've then karmically earned the right to forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.61,0:37:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,should you make a mistake.\NAnd one mistake that we've all made was we were too young at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.61,0:37:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We were too young at the time to know better.\NDoes that apply to everyone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.55,0:37:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're all too young.\NSo we forgive ourself because we're evolutionary creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.55,0:37:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of our love for God,\Nwe say, well, thank you, Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.55,0:37:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for the opportunity to grow and evolve\Nand to earn that which we become.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.55,0:37:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll meet you after lunch.\NTurned on?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.54,0:38:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You just turned on?\NThey made us late.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.18,0:38:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my nose just got longer.\NOh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.24,0:38:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my nose keeps getting longer.\NNo, they did not make us get late.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.24,0:38:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my nose just shrunk again.\NThings are a little slower than we expected at lunch anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.38,0:38:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow, do you remember where we were, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.89,0:38:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NYes, accountability means if you tell a lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.61,0:38:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,your nose gets longer.\NSo you can't sneak into heaven without their seeing your nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.25,0:39:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs to go to the bookstore.\NArt?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.42,0:39:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But you say it.\NWe need Art Tarby to go to the bookstore for us, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.31,0:39:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Art.\NArt, at the next break.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.31,0:39:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Art.\NArt Tarby.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.31,0:39:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Art.\NArt.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.31,0:39:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Art.\NArt.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.32,0:39:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good name.\NArt.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.32,0:39:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we certainly sound like we know what we're talking about here, don't we?\NLogos, ethos, and pathos.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.38,0:39:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We could ask all our politicians and ask them to explain those three concepts and see how\Nmany.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.74,0:40:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NWe covered deism, atheism, and accountability, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.61,0:40:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why people who won't take a pledge of allegiance to God and country, I always\Nmake them sit separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.60,0:40:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They may have a bomb in their pocket.\NI don't know what they're up to, but people who don't want to swear by God and country
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.86,0:40:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,really should elsewhere.\NIt doesn't mean nationalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.11,0:40:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It means because to love your fellow, to love your fellows is coming from the heart.\NComing from the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.94,0:40:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Pledge of allegiance is coming from the heart.\NSo you're not asking them to come from their mental self or their political self.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.94,0:40:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking them about their heart.\NDo you have a heart for your fellow man?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.94,0:40:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A heart for your country?\NLike they say, the reason a man was so dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.01,0:41:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who never to himself has said, this is my own, my native.\NTo just say it brings up tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.11,0:41:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo that's the heart of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.11,0:41:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're bringing up the universal heart.\NJust like when you hear the bagpipes, the same heart of mankind comes up and you weep
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.43,0:41:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the bagpipes.\NYou say, what am I crying for?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.43,0:41:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet everybody who has a heart does.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.04,0:41:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Except the English, I guess.\NYou don't want to hear the sound of the bagpipes coming over the hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.97,0:41:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing you want to hear is the sound of the bagpipes coming over the hill.\NMake sure your will is finalized and I'll leave my watch to, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.18,0:42:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart of mankind then is the great power of the heart.\NAnd if that's dead in a person, that's not too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.67,0:42:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Languaging, labels and semionics.\NWe already did that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.02,0:42:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's number three.\NNow where's number four?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.53,0:42:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here we are.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.62,0:42:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.48,0:42:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I know where we are.\NThe impact of framing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.63,0:42:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a thing can be made, turned from true to false by simply framing it in a different\Ncontext.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.82,0:42:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you get away, you get away with that one because you say literally it's the truth.\NBut how you position the truth, you turn the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.82,0:42:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou turn it into a falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.82,0:42:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's part of ingenuity, being ingenious.\NAnd devious.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.82,0:42:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Devious.\NNow deviousness is not an American tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.98,0:43:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a foreign culture in which deviousness is respected and cultivated.\NIn our culture, deviousness is not a praiseworthy character trait.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.98,0:43:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To be devious is a derogatory comment.\NIn others, it's considered to be an asset.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.40,0:43:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the accountability of mankind has been known, you know, throughout all of time in\Nseparate cultures, Native American culture, all the great cultures of the world, ancient
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.96,0:43:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Egypt.\NIn ancient Egypt, you know, Osiris is the god of, the lord of the underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.09,0:43:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you die, your heart is weighed on the scale.\NAnd so it's the truth, the heart of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.25,0:44:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the degree with which you have represented the truth, you either go this way or thumbs down.\NSo you are, every hair on your head again is counted in a totally different culture and a different context of ancient Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.43,0:44:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And Osiris is the god then who guards the underworld.\NAnd you either go to heaven or hell depending on its impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.43,0:44:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The weighing of the heart of truth then is something that should make people hesitate before they walk a devious pathway.\NBecause the realization that you're accountable in and of itself brings about integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.53,0:44:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Brings about integrity.\NThe weighing of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.01,0:44:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's, I saw that when I was in Egypt.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.30,0:44:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You could buy a very interesting diagrams of it.\NI was in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.46,0:44:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We had an appointment to meet.\NWell, he got assassinated before we got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.46,0:44:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.35,0:45:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got to meditate in the Great Pyramids and spent all night meditating in the Great Pyramid.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.45,0:45:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting experience.\NAnd I thought the ventilation, the ventilation left much to be desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.82,0:45:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd in the King's Chamber there's a sarcophagus that's been empty for a couple thousand years, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.19,0:45:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And people have to go to the bathroom.\NWell, there's no bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.19,0:45:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So they just go in the sarcophagus.\NSo as the centuries go by, centuries of people having to take a quick pee in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.78,0:45:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Egyptian government, I thought, you know, you could run a cylinder of air and just pump air all the way up into the King's Chamber.\NAnd flush that air out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.78,0:45:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, I don't know why they don't do that.\NWell, I see many, many years later they finally have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.98,0:46:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't remove the graffiti.\NWritten in a crayon is somebody, the guy's name, and it says 1937.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.30,0:46:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And they just leave it there.\NDisagreeing a great monument like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.38,0:46:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They just leave the graffiti instead of washing it off the wall.\NAnd I think I told you one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.74,0:46:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBehind the door someplace there in Egypt was a bunch of scrap, you know, paper and crumpled up stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.74,0:46:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And that has been there since Napoleon.\NThey haven't swept the floor since Napoleon was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.94,0:46:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after you go up the Nile and one of the heads had fallen off, one of the gods lined up along there.\NAnd then they, because the ice went down, they were raising the level of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.94,0:47:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So they had to move everything up, you know.\NSo at great expense, it was multinational effort to move everything up because the water was going to rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.22,0:47:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And they carefully put it all back with the same god with his head falling off in the same place.\NThey didn't put his head back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.45,0:47:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's so funny, you know.\NA totally different culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.61,0:47:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Americans would view that.\NYou know, we'd carefully put it back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.61,0:47:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd take off the graffiti.\NYeah, there's the head laying there in the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.12,0:47:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It was funny.\NAnd you had to leave the upper Nile by noon or 11 o'clock because it was 120 in the valley of death or whatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.66,0:48:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a tourist, you had to get out of there because they don't want tourists passing out from the heat and littering the place all over.\NAnd that was the place I told you where I had a ride in a camel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.52,0:48:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I've told you these stories before.\NAnyway, the camel, it was $10.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.90,0:48:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, $10.\NSo I rode around, you know, all over in this camel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.90,0:48:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the camel is very high.\NWhen you get on a camel, I mean, you are up in the air, you know, like on a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.90,0:48:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're way up there.\NAnd then when it came time to get off, he bought another $10.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.96,0:48:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I already paid you $10, huh?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.37,0:48:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, so I wanted to get off the camel.\NAnd I said, I already paid you $10.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.80,0:48:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So he says, cheap American.\NSo deviousness and ripping you off is endemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.30,0:49:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't feel guilty about that.\NAnd if he didn't work you for another $10, he'd probably be ashamed to go home and tell his mother that he didn't get that extra $10 out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.30,0:49:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, you have to have a camel driver.\NYou have to have the camel kneel down so you can get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.77,0:49:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So finally I decided I'll have to pay whether I like it or not, see?\NSo he starts bringing the camel down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.77,0:49:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the camel goes, .\NThat's Susan's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.23,0:50:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She put me up to it.\NShe said, do the camel.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.87,0:50:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the camel.\NOne time we were in San Francisco or Chicago, and I did the octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.26,0:50:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I haven't done the octopus since then.\NYou know, I can't do the octopus today.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.35,0:51:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I did the camel already.\NOh, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.42,0:51:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No more animals now.\NThe camel and the octopus on one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.90,0:51:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.47,0:51:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's ancient Egypt.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.06,0:51:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,With wisdom, you learn discretion.\NAnd prudence.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.41,0:52:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everything can be said at all times without some responsibility of discretion and prudence.\NSo this is the area of wisdom in which you begin to take moral responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.77,0:52:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To be loving towards the obligation is threefold, to yourself, to God, and to your fellow human beings, in my view.\NThose are your three obligations for which you're accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.20,0:52:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.\NThose are the three primary realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.19,0:52:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my understanding.\NThe three primary realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.15,0:52:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Love your neighbor as yourself.\NSermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.72,0:52:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Love God.\NLove your neighbor as yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.30,0:52:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So your obligation is that your life is a gift to your own spiritual evolution.\NSo you have an obligation to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.70,0:53:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And to fulfill your...\Nobligations and responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.21,0:53:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And to serve fellow man to the best of your ability.\NAnd by thus doing that, you serve God as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.01,0:53:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NTo yourself, to God, and to your fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.74,0:53:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All of creation is divine.\NSo therefore, I include the animal kingdom in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.28,0:53:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,To be kind to all that lives.\NAs well as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.59,0:53:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So wisdom and discretion then.\NBecause of prudence, we develop...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.59,0:53:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The gray hairs of age are earned.\NThey are earned.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.06,0:53:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegiance to God versus mammon.\NAnd that, of course, is the big conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.38,0:54:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God versus Caesar.\NSpiritual versus material.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.38,0:54:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether to do a thing for financial gain.\NI found you don't have to do anything for financial gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.46,0:54:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That fulfilling your obligation to yourself, to God and your fellow man.\NThat which you need emerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.85,0:54:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of nowhere.\NIt just seems to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.26,0:54:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And without seeking it, you see.\NSo if you write something of great excellence.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.94,0:54:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to read it, etc.\NSo you don't have to promote yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.48,0:54:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to...\NSo the desire for worldly gain in a way blocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.90,0:54:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization that you already have it.\NAs you evolve, you let go of desires and wants and attachments to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.80,0:55:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens is you create a space for it to emerge of its own.\NYou see, because the universe is really non-causal.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.95,0:55:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality emerges as the fulfillment of that potentiality.\NSo, although there were times...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.62,0:55:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When you had to steal food from the hospital.\NThat was a little skinny.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.35,0:55:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I ask God for forgiveness of that.\NI got $100 a month for 100 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.35,0:55:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 25 cents an hour.\NAll night, every other night and all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.48,0:55:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven days a week.\N$100 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.96,0:55:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, midnight they would serve this...\NWhoever's on at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.44,0:55:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They would have sandwiches with ham and stuff like that.\NSo I'd make one to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.54,0:55:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'd purposely put enough on my plate.\NAnd I'd take a paper napkin and quick put it in there and put it in my pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.54,0:55:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was dinner the next night.\NDinner the next night.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.54,0:56:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was thievery.\NI've confessed my sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.21,0:56:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistakes and errors are unwitting.\NUnwitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.21,0:56:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistakes and errors.\NSo sometimes people don't want to give allowance for mistakes and errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.21,0:56:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They think that an integrous person must be perfect.\NMust be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.21,0:56:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, mistakes and errors are not only possible.\NThey're almost certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.21,0:56:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the karmic propensities.\NKarmic propensities plus the limitation of humans in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.85,0:56:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And ourselves in particular.\NMistakes and errors are things for which we forgive ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.10,0:56:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that in counseling.\NI told you I had moral...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.23,0:56:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral...\NWhatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.94,0:56:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral over-conscience.\NOver-conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.22,0:57:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would berate myself for making the slightest mistake or error.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.48,0:57:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Scrupulosity.\NThat's what they called it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.48,0:57:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral scrupulosity.\NSo moral scrupulosity is not being spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.93,0:57:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being neurotic.\NSo I had to see a gopher counseling about moral scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.54,0:57:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That error is intrinsic to the human.\NAnd therefore the willingness to forgive yourself and forgive others.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.60,0:57:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive yourself and forgive others.\NSo the guy who cuts in front of you in traffic, you know, is showing poor judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.76,0:57:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do nothing about it, you'll meet him down the highway upside down.\NAnd I remember cars passing me on what is now a lovely road.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.36,0:58:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,On a gravel road and a curve.\NAnd as I got around the corner, it was a lovely sports car.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.36,0:58:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was upside down.\NWith his wheels still spinning.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.36,0:58:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha said you don't have to do anything against your enemies.\NBecause they will bring themselves down of their own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.84,0:58:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all live within a cultural morality of expectation and parameters.\NOf what's expected, what's permissible, what's forgivable, what's unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.45,0:58:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We have an idea of what is important.\NSo morality is also judgmentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.45,0:58:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is you're trying to decide priorities of morality.\NWhich is more moral?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.45,0:58:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This move or that move?\NAnd these are determined by our culture and our heritage.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.22,0:58:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the reason for emphasizing.\NThe heritage of the United States is it shows up in the Constitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.44,0:59:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Which calibrates in the amazing 700s.\NAnd it shows up in the Bill of Rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.66,0:59:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's represented by the pilgrims seeking religious freedom.\NSo our cultural morality is based on centuries of spiritual integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.36,0:59:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This reversal of truth takes place and affects the brain.\NNow you can say which is primary?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.97,0:59:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is primary?\NIs the brain physiology?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.19,0:59:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The limitation of brain physiology causing this impairment?\NOr is it the other way around?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.19,0:59:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The person's intention affects the brain physiology.\NLet's ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.09,0:59:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.\NIt's the person's intention that affects the brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.25,0:59:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NIt's not the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.66,0:59:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.66,0:59:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're not the victim of your brain.\NYou're not the victim of your brain function.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.11,1:00:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are not the victim of our brain physiology.\NWe are the determinant of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.94,1:00:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOh, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.94,1:00:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that's clarified.\NSo whether you become left brain or right brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.42,1:00:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the map of brain physiology shows different pathways.\NSo what you have chosen to become then reflects itself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.48,1:00:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in your brain physiology and not the other way around.\NHuh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.57,1:00:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that removes that cop out.\NJust my brain physiology, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.58,1:00:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo we choose good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.58,1:00:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We choose it.\NWe choose it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.58,1:00:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And people choose evil because at the higher levels because there's gain.\NBut at the lower levels because they get a certain great pleasure from it,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.70,1:01:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain glee.\NThe glee of being bad is its own payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.80,1:01:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.12,1:01:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Using conscience as one's guide then, you need a rational conscience.\NSo the more sophisticated you become, religious and philosophically and spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.05,1:01:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the conscience becomes a greater and greater source of reliability.\NSo, you know, I was in a Freudian school.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.72,1:01:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a Freudian psychoanalysis.\NAnd Freud talked about the ego differently than we do in spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.72,1:01:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego was a strength that balanced the superego, which is the conscience, against the id,\Nagainst the id, which is the animal impulsivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.82,1:01:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one sense of reality.\NSo the conscience then is what berates you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.71,1:01:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.06,1:02:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she's gone mad, Your Honor.\NShe's gone mad.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.13,1:02:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gone mad.\NConscience, let your conscience be your guide.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.13,1:02:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopefully you have a mature and educated conscience, which is interested in integrity rather than\Njust morality because moralism, becoming moralistic, being moralistic can be a great hindrance.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.13,1:02:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I pulled up from the universal archetype.\NWhen I was doing truth versus falsehood, I mean, I spent a lot of months outside clearing the stuff that got pulled up from the collective.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.22,1:02:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Indignant.\NIndignant evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.50,1:02:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Indignant.\NSo the spiritual night came up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.82,1:03:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The archetype of the night would come up and the spleen of the spiritual night would be an indignation.\NIndignation.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.50,1:03:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the way a dog fighting right now.\NWhen you see a dog fighting, you see these dogs rip to shreds.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.30,1:03:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,First, what comes up in you is the spleen of indignation.\NYou know, you're indignant and angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.33,1:03:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How they could exploit dumb animals like that.\NSo that's one of the last things to really clear out, the thing that took the longest.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.26,1:03:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I was doing truth versus falsehood,\Nyou see one indignation after another.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.26,1:03:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, with this bull baiting, a dog fighting or some form of rampant cruelty was always something I found very difficult to handle.\NEspecially cruelty, willful cruelty to animals, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.26,1:04:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And they train these dogs.\NThey take the victim dog and tape its mouth shut.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.26,1:04:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Put tape around its snout so it can't defend itself.\NAnd let the other dogs have at them.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.35,1:04:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That don't bring up the spleen of indignation.\NMoral indignation in yourself, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.35,1:04:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's enough to bring up a rage.\NSo as we said, on judgment day, every hair should be counted.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.44,1:04:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We do that over and over again.\NBecause somehow, we get that unconsciously.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.44,1:04:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes innate.\NIt becomes innate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.57,1:04:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes prioritized.\NThe likelihood of that awareness coming up becomes increasingly so.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.79,1:04:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it becomes a great guide to a reasonable conscience.\NAnd we call that, you know, the more often you make a certain choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.43,1:04:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the more likely you're going to make that choice again.\NSo realizing that every hair on your head is counted.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.82,1:05:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the picture of Osiris weighing the heart.\NAnd realizing our accountability.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.30,1:05:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is not to frighten us.\NBut to make us realize our moral responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.30,1:05:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the consequences thereof.\NBecause our decisions affect everyone around us.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.30,1:05:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Our decisions.\NBecause there is a collective consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.30,1:05:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So every time we choose the higher,\Nwe tend to lift the level of the water of the sea of the collective consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.94,1:05:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, mankind collectively has been making a lot of bad,\Nwhat we call bad,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.54,1:05:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral,\Nnon-aggress decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.06,1:05:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we see the level of consciousness of mankind has gone down recently.\NEspecially western civilization.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.31,1:05:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So that makes us aware that our inner decisions\Nis affecting the level of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.31,1:06:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time we make a decision,\Nwe're affecting all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.31,1:06:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,People like to think of themselves separately.\NBut that's narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.63,1:06:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all part of the one of humanness.\NMankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.63,1:06:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of our decisions affects everyone alive.\NSo to counteract the descendant of non-integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.89,1:06:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it's more and more important that a group like this exists.\NAnd that we calibrate it before.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.89,1:06:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In other classes,\Nthis group alone counterbalances
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.11,1:06:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,something like millions of people.\NThis group here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.14,1:06:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask.\NThis group,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.50,1:06:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask.\NCounterbalances relatively millions of people in the negative domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.53,1:06:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This group alone counterbalances millions.\NBecause this group is so much power.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.32,1:07:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,High energy power.\NA group like this literally counterbalances millions
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.58,1:07:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of people devoted to negativity, hatred, etc.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.77,1:07:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't we something, huh?\NGuess that shows them, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.62,1:07:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess that shows those folks where to go.\NNow it's just interesting that it's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.58,1:07:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause it's what you've become.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.58,1:07:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Not what you do, what you think, what you say.\NWhat you have become is the reality of your essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.58,1:07:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And that essence shines forth.\NAll that exists radiates forth an energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.77,1:07:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists.\NAll that ever existed radiates forth an energy forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.99,1:07:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we can ask about anything, anywhere in time, distance, space, and history.\NBecause all that ever existed, that radiation is still there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.22,1:08:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think we did it in one class, huh?\NWe calibrated Napoleon before he went into the pyramid
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.05,1:08:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and Napoleon after he left the pyramid, huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.43,1:08:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because he saw,\Nhe had a vision of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.43,1:08:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Waterloo.\NHe had a vision,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.62,1:08:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a vision that he was not invincible\Nand saw the vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.62,1:08:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Napoleon who walked into the pyramid\Nwas not the same Napoleon who walked out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.14,1:08:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very interesting.\NSo you can calibrate his energy before he went in
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.20,1:08:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and after he came out and had that vision.\NSort of a pre-vision of coming events.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.42,1:08:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the narcissistic glorification of free speech\Nis probably the biggest threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.87,1:08:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In my view of it,\Nto Western civilization in general
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.87,1:09:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the US of A in particular.\NThe glorification of free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.10,1:09:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now free speech is not God.\NYou see a society in which we have
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.24,1:09:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Godified free speech.\NAnything is okay as long as it's free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.72,1:09:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech.\NHatred, lying, extortion, blackmail.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.77,1:09:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything is okay so long as it's free speech.\NSo we have come to worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.86,1:09:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is one of the niceties of democracy.\NBut it is not the peak of the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.86,1:09:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to die for free speech.\NI don't give a damn if you never express your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.21,1:09:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even care what your opinion is.\NAm I going to die for your opinion
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.38,1:09:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can get out there and write a nasty blog site?\NGive me a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.57,1:10:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is not the highest.\NIt's the greatest good which mankind can reach.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.21,1:10:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing when to shut up, I think, is better.\NWe have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.13,1:10:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Discretion of speech is a higher good.\NDiscretion of speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.67,1:10:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Using your speech for goodness,\Nfor love, for that which is beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.28,1:10:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech for its own sake\Nis nothing but narcissistic self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.28,1:10:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You get up there and make\Nmulti-millions of dollars a year
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.89,1:10:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,having a daily hate panel\Nin which you get to sit up there and spew forth hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.89,1:10:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I dying for that?\NDid I die for that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.30,1:10:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to die for that.\NWas I in World War II for that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.75,1:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on hazardous duty, blow up any second.\NWas I willing to do that for that woman to say that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.52,1:10:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.90,1:11:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't.\NNor do I dedicate all that risk
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.90,1:11:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to the misuse of free speech.\NThe exploitation and the degradation of free speech,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.12,1:11:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so free speech has become a degradation\Nto express hate and vilification and untruth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.76,1:11:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So a society which gives equal time,\Nequal time to both sides,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.81,1:11:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,means that they end up with no truth about anything.\NSo this misuse of free speech
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.06,1:11:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is a narcissistic self-indulgence.\NTo build up your own self-esteem
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.25,1:11:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of your narcissistic ego.\NNarcissistic glorification of free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.27,1:12:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So free speech during the 50s,\Nwhen I was growing up,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.17,1:12:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,free speech calibrated at 255.\NFree speech now, due to degradation,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.52,1:12:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 180.\NLet's see what happened to free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.81,1:12:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember President Ford,\Nis it Ford that stumbled?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.22,1:12:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYou know, Roosevelt,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.79,1:12:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,they were all smokers by the way,\NRoosevelt had polio and he was crippled.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.66,1:12:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the press,\Nthe photographers just did not focus
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.23,1:12:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,on his crippled licks, you see?\NHere you're fighting for survival of America, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.23,1:12:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the greatest time.\NSo with discretion, with discretion,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.23,1:12:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,not due to loss of freedom,\Nbut out of discretion,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.23,1:12:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody focused on it.\NI saw the end of that era
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.84,1:12:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when President Ford,\Nwas it Ford?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.84,1:13:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.06,1:13:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the change in the era.\NFord was coming out of US-1
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.16,1:13:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever that airline is.\NAnd he got down about five or six steps
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.16,1:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and he stumbled.\NNow, in the old days,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.06,1:13:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they would just leave the clip out.\NYou don't need that clip in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.41,1:13:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But the media focused on it.\NYou saw Ford trip,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.47,1:13:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the TV an hour later,\NFord trip, Ford trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.66,1:13:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that was the biggest event,\Nworld event,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.66,1:13:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that he merely stumbled a bit on a step or two.\NAnd then in that instant I knew
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.66,1:13:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they just put the dagger in the heart of freedom.\NThey just put the dagger in the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.73,1:13:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have the legal right to see it?\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.43,1:13:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You got the legal right to do a lot of things.\NI can take my pants off
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.43,1:13:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as I got my shirt on.\NI got the legal right to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.43,1:13:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that wisdom?\NIs that discretion?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.48,1:14:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the press go down right then\Nfor a headline for a few more seconds
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.62,1:14:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Observer.\NThey took down Ford's dignity.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.68,1:14:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So to take down the dignity\Nof the head of your own country
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.97,1:14:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is suicidal.\NThat's imbecility
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.97,1:14:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the glorification of narcissism.\NAnd that's what Ford did.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.97,1:14:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we've been doing it ever since.\NEvery president,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.97,1:14:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,God help him if he sneezes.\NImagine what would happen
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.29,1:14:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,if the president sneezed\Nright in the middle of an interview.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.29,1:14:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what would happen.\NThe news would keep it right on,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.25,1:14:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't they?\NWe could all laugh at him sneezing
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.25,1:14:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and blowing his nose.\NThey would.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.01,1:14:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good for a few more watchers.\NSo the narcissistic glorification
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.90,1:14:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of free speech to me\Nis the Achilles heel,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.90,1:15:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Achilles heel of our current society\Nin the Western world
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.90,1:15:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and in America in particular.\NIf free speech means equal time,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.06,1:15:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,equal weight\Nto the enemies of our own culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.12,1:15:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't it?\NIt's like,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.16,1:15:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,without sounding like a sexist,\Nit's like a woman getting up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.16,1:15:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I always get a woman, Muslim,\Nglorifying Islamic law, Sharia.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.60,1:15:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It says it takes two to three women\Nto make one man.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.95,1:15:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And she wants to inculcate that\Nin our culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.97,1:15:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Women are created dumber than men\Nand it takes two or three women
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.97,1:15:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to equal one man.\NAnd here's this woman championing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.97,1:15:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs a good doctor.\NWhy would a woman want to champion
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.18,1:16:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,an ideology that ridicules them,\Nmakes them inferior,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.18,1:16:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and some kind of cheap property\Nthat you don't even have to account for?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.44,1:16:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,More or less like dog fighting, yeah?\NIf you beat a woman, it doesn't count.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.73,1:16:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter if you beat a woman.\NIt's just like beating a dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.30,1:16:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So why a person would want to bring that\Ninto the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.30,1:16:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it the law of the land is beyond.\NBut that's part of free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.85,1:16:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the downside of free speech\Nis that it's a two-edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.88,1:16:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It can cut falsehood,\Nbut it can also cut yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.88,1:16:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a two-edged sword.\NThat's why the Course in Miracles
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.88,1:16:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,talks about forgiveness\Nas a one-edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.88,1:16:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness, it's incapable.\NIt only cuts in one direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.94,1:16:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So forgiveness then.\NSo we forgive people that are brainwashed
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.52,1:16:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of indoctrinated\Nwith concepts that all calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.52,1:17:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloggerism seems to be just an expression\Nof this desecration of what to me
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.41,1:17:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,should be revered.\NFree speech should be revered.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.50,1:17:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloggerism is just the means of destroying it.\NThere's one blogger site
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.02,1:17:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that ends with cos, K-O-S.\NAnyway, it calibrates at 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.50,1:17:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,90.\NWhat have you got to say to the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.50,1:17:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The world wants to hear it.\NIt calibrates at 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.50,1:17:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The daily cos, you know, daily cos.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.85,1:17:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Daily cos calibrates.\NWe have permission over this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.14,1:17:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 90.\N95.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.36,1:17:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,90.\NDedicated to evil and its promulgation.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.10,1:17:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so evil and its promulgation\Ncalibrated at 90
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.22,1:18:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,has equal time, equal time, equal importance\Nwith truth, which calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.70,1:18:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we saw in my lifetime\Nfree speech dropped from 255,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.70,1:18:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which is respect for the responsibility\Nof free speech,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.70,1:18:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to 180,\Nwhich is the misuse of it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.74,1:18:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for really subserving what the world\Nhas traditionally called eagle.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.74,1:18:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Eagle.\NEagle.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.25,1:18:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego evil.\NEgo evil, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.22,1:18:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing bloggers do is they salt the mine.\NThey plant a story in one place
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.22,1:18:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can then quote that as an authority\Nfor the other site.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.22,1:18:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As quoted from Blah Blah,\Nlike it's not their fault,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.29,1:18:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as quoted from so and so.\NSo that's called salting the mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.54,1:18:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There's professional people out there\Nwho for a price,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.77,1:18:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who for a price\Nwill become a poison pen
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.90,1:19:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and dream up and try to seek out\Nanything negative they can about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.90,1:19:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.\NThat you once got a parking ticket.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.54,1:19:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He is reportedly a lawbreaker.\NThat's the way it comes across.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.14,1:19:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Reportedly a lawbreaker.\NYou add reportedly,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.14,1:19:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so you sound like you're being very sensible\Nand balanced about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.14,1:19:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to say something nasty about him.\NReportedly a lawbreaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.42,1:19:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it says.\NSenator so and so is reportedly a lawbreaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.38,1:19:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Reportedly a lawbreaker.\NReportedly.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.24,1:19:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Or known locally as a lawbreaker.\NSee, that way you can't pin anybody down.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.27,1:19:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthere are people out there
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.07,1:19:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that are paid big money,\Nbig money from the far left,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.33,1:20:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,big money to shoot down integrity\Nusing the mechanisms of salting the mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.45,1:20:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The other one is the straw man\Nand of course the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.45,1:20:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So you plant a story\Nin one part of bloggerdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.58,1:20:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You then go to another blog site\Nand you quote this blog
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.68,1:20:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as the authority from which\Nyou can now say this
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.68,1:20:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because you didn't say it,\Nyou're just quoting them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.10,1:20:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you planted it,\Nit's forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.10,1:20:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called salting the mine.\NIt's done.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.32,1:20:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had personal experience with it\Nand I'm an authority on how it works.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.67,1:20:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I can spot professionalism.\NI know it's a professional job.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.67,1:20:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell right away.\NHe claims,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.56,1:20:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,he claims to be a doctor.\NHe claims.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.58,1:20:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that he is.\NHe claims.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.87,1:21:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The word claims appears all over.\NClaims.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.42,1:21:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is to cast aspersion\Nby subtle innuendo.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.42,1:21:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NHe claims this,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.45,1:21:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,claims to be a law abider\Nand yet we see
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.45,1:21:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that he has broken the law in the past.\NIn fact, I'm going to confess my past.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.37,1:21:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?\NI got a parking ticket in Cottonwood
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.57,1:21:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for parking too close to a loading zone.\NThis was 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.13,1:21:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a ticket\Nand I had to go to magistrate's court.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.96,1:21:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to magistrate's court.\NWell, what was happening,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.62,1:21:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a red loading zone\Nand you're supposed to park away
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.62,1:21:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from the red loading zone\Nand I parked a little over the red loading zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.62,1:22:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Not used to the air here, I guess.\NI would ordinarily not park near the end of a loading zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.66,1:22:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So somehow I must have been,\Nbut I did,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.53,1:22:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I did park next to this loading zone.\NA red paint thing that said loading zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.23,1:22:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I took my ticket,\NI took it home
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.23,1:22:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and it gave me my appearance state\Nbefore the magistrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.23,1:22:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hanging out my dirty linen\Nso you can dirty laundry.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.29,1:22:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't get hit with it there\Nthat I was covering up anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.29,1:22:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A law breaker.\NAnd so I drove back down to Cottonwood
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.96,1:22:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on the magistrate's court date.\NShowed up in the courthouse there on Main Street
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.96,1:22:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and went in and found the magistrate's court\Nand I told him I had this ticket
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.96,1:22:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wished to pay.\NAnd he looked at me and said,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.44,1:22:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for a parking ticket?\NI said yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.44,1:22:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He said the fine will be one dollar\Nand we'll waive it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.78,1:22:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn't believe that a guy actually showed up in court\Nto answer a one dollar parking ticket.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.78,1:23:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But it said you were supposed to appear\Nin the magistrate's court so I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.36,1:23:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NHowever,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.71,1:23:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the confession of my law breaking days.\NThat's all of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.14,1:23:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nso anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.37,1:23:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for a certain price,\Nuh, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.37,1:23:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can destroy anybody for a certain price.\NAnd I know exactly what the price is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.10,1:23:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it's paid.\NIt's transferred electronically.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.10,1:23:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even paid by check.\NAnd for that price,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.10,1:23:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they get a professional chopper\Nwho can take anything in your make,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.10,1:23:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,life and make it sound derogatory.\NSo and so has a weight problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.00,1:23:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand he once had a financial problem\Nand of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.00,1:23:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he has a legal record.\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.26,1:24:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he did get a,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.26,1:24:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't tell you it's a parking ticket.\NAnd then,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.26,1:24:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so everything gets exaggerated\Nout of thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.26,1:24:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you calibrate those things,\Nyou'll find they're 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.26,1:24:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all 190.\NAnd their source is 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.83,1:24:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they'll give themselves\Na religious name as a source.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.83,1:24:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You calibrate them at 190\Nand then you find out using our method of telling truth
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.83,1:24:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,how much they got paid for the story.\NI suppose a lot of people would do it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.50,1:24:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for that kind of money.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.04,1:24:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nin as much as we're answerable
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.38,1:24:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time,\Nfor the consequences of our actions,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.51,1:24:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,not out of fear,\Nnot out of superstition,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.83,1:24:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,not out of being brainwashed,\Nbut out of free choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.28,1:24:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we own the dignity and greatness\Nof our own reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.79,1:24:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We give it the respect that it is due.\NYour life is a gift from almighty God.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.79,1:25:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's hardly a small thing.\NIf God gave you a great big China thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.18,1:25:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nyou wouldn't be sticking it up
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.18,1:25:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,where the wind can blow it over,\Nwould you?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.18,1:25:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be putting it,\NGod gave me this.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.18,1:25:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nthis is almighty God gave me this thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.18,1:25:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Nyou would be very careful with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.72,1:25:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou grant the same respect to your own life.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.72,1:25:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And intrinsically,\NI know the worth of others
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.91,1:25:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and I see that their weakness,\Nthe weakness to make money,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.91,1:25:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the pleasure in maligning other people,\Nthe pleasure in maligning people,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.98,1:25:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what they get off on.\NThey get sort of a
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.98,1:25:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,glee some joy out of wickedness\Nfor its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.30,1:25:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wickedness for its own sake.\NThat explains these bloggers
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.65,1:25:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the people that they pay\Nto do those kind of hatchet jobs
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.28,1:25:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is the pleasure out of wickedness,\Nper se,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.95,1:25:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,resist.\NSee,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.95,1:26:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no cause.\NThere's nothing causing them to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.14,1:26:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're expressing the wickedness\Nof what they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.98,1:26:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get that,\Nyou get away from causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.45,1:26:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole Newtonian thing,\Nthe whole Newtonian idea,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.45,1:26:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole politicalization\Nthat it's society's fault,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.45,1:26:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always the majority's fault,\Nor something like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.45,1:26:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's been the minority.\NI've been the minority a million times.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.54,1:26:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.79,1:26:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,whoever you decide you are,\Neverybody else then becomes the majority,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.95,1:26:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,don't they?\NHow many middle-aged,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.14,1:26:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,retired school teachers are there,\Nage 46,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.23,1:26:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,who taught Latin?\NYou're a minority.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.23,1:26:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us are a minority of one.\NWe're all a minority of one.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.47,1:26:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NEverybody is a minority of one.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.02,1:26:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou defend your fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.11,1:27:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you defend your own self,\Nand because that's what you intuit
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.14,1:27:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is your responsibility to divinity.\NYour responsibilities are ending up today
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.14,1:27:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with fulfilling your sensibility to yourself\Nbecause your life is your responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.37,1:27:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and your life is a gift from God\Nand your own recognition
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.37,1:27:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the importance of your own spirit.\NYou recognize your responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.20,1:27:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,towards your fellow man\Nto relieve suffering whenever you can,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.20,1:27:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to do what you can,\Nand to God
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.20,1:27:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because your responsibility to God\Nis like forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.55,1:27:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever.\NForever is sort of quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.24,1:27:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The respect for divinity,\Nfor God,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.24,1:27:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for truth and all the things\Nthat I talk about
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.40,1:27:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is considerably intensified\Nby my own experience of the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.58,1:28:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I already told you in previous lectures.\NAt the bottom of ultimate despair
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.76,1:28:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the time I was an atheist\Nand having given up all hope
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.76,1:28:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of ever finding anything that recognized truth,\NI went into the very root and source
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.02,1:28:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowingness, consciousness,\Nthinking, life, energy, consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.85,1:28:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I went wherever it would lead.\NI went into a dark and infinite space
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.03,1:28:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and as I went in,\NI recognized I was going into hell
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.03,1:28:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because there were demons everywhere\Nscreaming to people being tortured,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.03,1:28:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,much like the screams of these dogs\Nthat are allowed to kill each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.26,1:28:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,People who allow that\Nare going to hear the screams.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.26,1:28:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to hear the screams\Nin the same place I heard the screams.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.26,1:28:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear the screams of the agony\Nof the suffering you brought others.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.90,1:28:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And you think this is hell.\NIt is hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.44,1:29:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's only the jacks for openers.\NIt's only the very top level of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.44,1:29:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I've said before,\Nlike Donnie's Inferno,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.44,1:29:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as you go further and further into hell,\Nwhat happens is the agony now is no longer linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.86,1:29:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a knowingness of abandonment\Nto the agony of being deserted
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.91,1:29:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of all hope ever, forever.\NAnd in that,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.74,1:29:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in that depths of the pits of hell,\Nyou get what forever means.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.19,1:29:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Means always, always.\NContinuous, unstopping, never always.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.80,1:29:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The agony of the soul,\Ncompletely abandoned,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.63,1:29:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond description.\NTime there stops,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.98,1:29:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the experientially,\Njust like at the top space in the presence of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.98,1:29:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,there is foreverness.\NAt the bottom in the pit is foreverness.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.98,1:30:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So you experience the agony of the soul,\Nforever.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.18,1:30:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Goes on for eternity.\NExperientially,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.66,1:30:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience the eternity of the damnation of the soul.\NAnd out of the very ultimate depths of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.94,1:30:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,arose a voice from this consciousness,\Nnot from the person,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.94,1:30:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because the person was long gone.\NIf there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.00,1:30:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask him for help.\NAnd then oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.74,1:30:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly,\Nthe glory of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.10,1:30:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She went forth.\NIn full splendor,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.51,1:30:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as all of that,\Nthat which is the essence of all existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.51,1:30:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the transformation,\Nwas incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.27,1:30:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I repeat this story about hell,\Nis because I don't want anybody to take the slightest chance of going there.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.46,1:30:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's merely to underscore,\Nthe value of integrity for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.50,1:31:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not out of fear of hell,\Nbut out of knowing that,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.50,1:31:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we are completely,\Nand truly answerable to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.50,1:31:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We are answerable to all God.\NSo that adds a certain,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.50,1:31:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sincerity and importance.\NYou begin to see that your decisions are not just frivolous.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.50,1:31:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not just jokes.\NThey're not just immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.50,1:31:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That your life counts.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.53,1:31:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,every decision in your life counts.\NSo you begin to own the worth,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.53,1:31:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the impact of your own life.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.75,1:31:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when you dismiss everything as nothing,\Nand everything is a joke,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.75,1:31:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything is just a TV thing and all this.\NWhen you trivialize your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.85,1:31:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trivializing that which is the most valuable thing that you own,\Nand that is your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.85,1:31:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say this only to,\Nunderscore,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.46,1:31:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to guard the sacredness of your life.\NYour life is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.92,1:32:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it's sacred,\Nyou have the capacity to uplift,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.92,1:32:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone on the planet.\NBy just what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.92,1:32:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,To verify the sacredness of your life then,\Nis to verify the sacredness of everyone's life,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.59,1:32:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby you lift the level of the sea,\Nand relieve the suffering of others,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.59,1:32:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who are on the other side of the world,\Nand don't even know that you exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.59,1:32:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nas we forgive and,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.94,1:32:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,send forth that love,\NI always picture before I go to bed,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.94,1:32:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the relief of the suffering of all sentient beings,\Nand the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.94,1:32:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I picture a little child laying somewhere,\Nhopeless and next to death,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.74,1:32:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling abandoned,\Nor some animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.86,1:32:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,laying there suffering.\NThen I realize,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.50,1:32:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that our intention,\Nat that last moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.05,1:32:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it can handle the suffering.\NIt can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.11,1:33:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It can.\NBecause of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.14,1:33:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's our gift.\NBack to thee,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.67,1:33:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,oh Lord.\NAmen.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.18,1:33:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take a break,\Nand then we're going to reassemble,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.68,1:33:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and have a dialogue.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.80,1:33:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dialogue, questions and answers,\Nand the part I like the most,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.99,1:33:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,chatting with all the people here,\Nthe individuals,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.28,1:33:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what's rattling in their coconut.\NSo we'll see you shortly,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.95,1:33:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as we get reset up.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.74,1:33:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Doc.\NSpeak, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.90,1:34:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Doc.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.23,1:34:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you please explain,\Nwould you please explain,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.28,1:34:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you've explained about Luciferic,\Nand demonic energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.28,1:34:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWould you please explain,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.28,1:34:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,something you talked about,\Nas far as the energy of confusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.28,1:34:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and how that affects us?\NGenerally the negative energies,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.54,1:34:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,are considered to be Luciferic.\NIt's pridefulness,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.54,1:34:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,arrogance,\Nseeking dominance, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.86,1:34:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeking power for its own sake.\NAnd satanic,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.86,1:34:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which is evil,\Npain, and suffering,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.86,1:34:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and torture.\NI think it's an esoteric concept.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.05,1:34:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a third,\Nand that is the energy of confusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.50,1:34:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is called the Braxic.\NA-B-A-R-A-A-X-I-S-I-C.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.50,1:34:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it comes out of Alice Bailey.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.50,1:34:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the energy of confusion.\NConfusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.50,1:34:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And disorder.\NEverything goes wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.75,1:34:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's on time.\NYour zipper won't zip.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.75,1:34:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is screwed up.\NAnd no matter what you tell people,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.75,1:34:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they get it all wrong.\NAnd,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.75,1:35:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an Abraxic energy.\NThe way you clear it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.75,1:35:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you deny its reality,\Nyou deny its sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.75,1:35:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But,\Nit's a Braxic energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.86,1:35:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nit's a Braxic energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.86,1:35:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nit's a Braxic energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.27,1:35:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nit's a Braxic energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.27,1:35:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nit's a Braxic energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.27,1:35:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nyou deny its sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.34,1:35:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say,\Nmy life is under the control of divine order and harmony.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.23,1:35:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality of the self,\Nor the capital S,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.23,1:35:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is divine order and harmony,\Nrules my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.23,1:35:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\NI hereby reject
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.36,1:35:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,confusion and disorder as a reality.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.13,1:35:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But,\Nyou can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.13,1:35:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want to take over a population,\Nfirst thing you do is confuse them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.13,1:35:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthat's what the political strategists do.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.13,1:35:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They have opposing grits of\Npower,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.13,1:36:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,lock and then out of that confusion out of that confusion you can take control of the field\Nso if all the players are running in different directions it's obvious anybody's got his head
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.06,1:36:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,screwed on can take over dominance of the field it's called the bractic energy thank you thanks\Nfor asking me that thank you doctor thank you susan that's enough hi doc yes i just want to
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.72,1:36:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,let you and susan know first of all that i really really love you guys and i so appreciate everything\Nthat you are thank you um i have a comment for you and then a question um over the past few years i've
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.90,1:37:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,had the opportunity once a year to go to south africa and to teach workshops and i wanted to\Nteach workshops oh yes and i wanted you to know how that people are becoming aware how they're
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.16,1:37:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,reading your work\Nand the growth in consciousness that is happening there there is now
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.02,1:37:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in cape town a study group south africa yes yes that's right they do correspond with us yes and\Nit's been beautiful to see um i have a question for you about mixing levels could you perhaps
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.88,1:37:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,elucidate a little bit more how to work with um the issue of mixing levels in a counseling setting\Nto help
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.20,1:37:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,help the client\Nunderstand especially when they don't have a very good framework of your work
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.16,1:37:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to help them understand and get clarity\Nwell
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.45,1:37:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use uh... under what conditions is that\Ninstead of level
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.34,1:37:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say\Nunder what conditions is this oh expected or
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.94,1:38:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate eh\Nand sometimes people mix levels and end up with confusion but so how do you understand 沒有
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.34,1:38:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because what's appropriate or true in one context is not in another so I asked\Nthem to refine the definitions okay and then in the definition of that which you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.08,1:38:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,simply apply to the physical to their personal lives rather than the spiritual\Ncontext because some people don't seem to have as much of that spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.26,1:38:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,context to relate well they're just along the pathway mm-hmm you can use\Nsimpler language you know okay you can create another big as-if or make-believe
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.68,1:38:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,situation and say now in that situation what would you do Oh how would you see\Nit so you can create an alternative and ask them how things look if that were so
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.62,1:39:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in other words using their own framework to mirror it back to them yes or for\Nteaching purposes you can create a different framework okay you know I'd
